sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant P1 as Player 1<br/>(mobile)
    participant P2 as Player 2<br/>(mobile)
    participant O as Operator
    participant B as Backend
    participant M as Middleware
    participant U as UE

    Note over P1,U: Scenario: Session active, operator cancels mid-game<br/>(e.g., emergency, technical issue, wrong room assignment)

    Note over U: Session ACTIVE, Level 1 in progress
    Note over B: 2 players in session, each paid 10 minutes

    O->>B: POST /sessions/{id}/cancel {reason: "technical_issue"}
    B->>B: BEGIN TRANSACTION
    B->>B: session.status → CANCELLED
    B->>B: session.endedAt = NOW
    B->>B: session.endReason = OPERATOR_CANCELLED

    Note over B: Refund all players

    B->>B: For each MatchPlayer in session:
    loop Each player
        B->>B: INSERT Transaction (type=refund, amount=10, sessionId)
        B->>B: UPDATE user.balanceMinutes += 10
    end

    B->>B: COMMIT

    par Notify operator
        B-->>O: 200 {refundedMinutes: 20, affectedUsers: 2}
    and Stop game
        B--)M: WS push: session_cancel<br/>{reason: "operator_request"}
        M--)U: session_cancel
        U->>U: Stop current level immediately
        U->>U: Hide HUD
        U->>U: Show "Session cancelled by operator"<br/>screen (10 sec)
        U->>U: Return to Idle
    and Notify players
        B--)P1: WS or push: {event: session_cancelled, refund: 10}
        P1->>P1: Show "Session cancelled. 10 minutes refunded."
        B--)P2: WS or push
        P2->>P2: Show refund notification
    end

    Note over U: UE receives confirmation, shuts down cleanly
    U--)M: session_ended {reason: "cancelled"}
    M->>B: POST /sessions/{id}/end<br/>(Idempotency: sess-end)

    alt Session already COMPLETED on backend (cancel was first)
        B-->>M: 200 {status: CANCELLED (unchanged), ratingDelta: null}
    end

    Note over U,B: No rating calculated for cancelled sessions.<br/>Players have full balance refund.<br/>Matches data preserved for debug, but marked as "session_ended" fail reason.
